CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1956, pg. 3 reads: "In Their Easter Bonnets...and pretty frocks, too, these darling little girls paraded their spring finery at a fashion review at A. Leo Weil School. Some wore quilted skirts and toppers while others preferred sheer dressy frocks.  Left to right: ...Diane Hutton..."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Diane Hutton modeling light colored swiss dot dress with full skirt, and ankle socks, standing on stage in A. Leo Weil School for Easter fashion show
